00:08:37.060 --> 00:08:40.580
 a water soluble dye will leak in it.

00:08:40.580 --> 00:08:44.540
 That has been demonstrated for more than 100 years

00:08:44.540 --> 00:08:49.380
 on simple organisms as well as tissue culture.

00:08:49.380 --> 00:08:53.340
 So it's really an old idea.

00:08:53.340 --> 00:08:58.340
 But about 50 years ago, someone demonstrated in rats

00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:05.460
 that the lipid loving quality of the brain

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:09.540
 is what governs the so-called barrier function.

00:09:09.540 --> 00:09:14.540
 The brain has to live at a very high energy state.

00:09:14.540 --> 00:09:19.080
 And in that high energy state,

00:09:19.080 --> 00:09:22.660
 it's more hydrophobic or fat loving.

00:09:22.660 --> 00:09:27.700
 These researchers put an emulsion of,

00:09:27.700 --> 00:09:32.700
 I think it was soy oil, into the carotid artery of a rat

00:09:32.700 --> 00:09:38.420
 and then measured the content of the blood coming out

00:09:38.420 --> 00:09:42.240
 of the vein draining the brain.

00:09:42.240 --> 00:09:47.140
 And they found that on a single pass through the brain,

00:09:47.140 --> 00:09:51.780
 17% of this fat was taken up from the blood.

00:09:51.780 --> 00:09:56.460
 And if you imagine that when you're under stress,

00:09:57.500 --> 00:10:02.500
 your blood becomes loaded with unbound fatty acids,

00:10:02.500 --> 00:10:10.980
 free fatty acids that travel on the albumin in the blood.

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:18.140
