00:12:36.560 --> 00:12:40.700
 of the effect of intestinal serotonin

00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:42.560
 getting into the brain.

00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:47.560
 And serotonin itself powerfully breaks down barriers,

00:12:47.560 --> 00:12:53.000
 including the blood-brain barrier, so-called.

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:59.420
 The lungs and the brain happen to be the best equipped

00:12:59.420 --> 00:13:05.160
 with enzymes that destroy serotonin.

00:13:05.160 --> 00:13:10.220
 Monoamine oxidase is very concentrated in these capillaries.

00:13:12.180 --> 00:13:17.180
 So normally when the blood passes through the lungs,

00:13:17.180 --> 00:13:22.960
 it happens that the surge of oxygen changes the pH

00:13:22.960 --> 00:13:27.960
 and carbon dioxide content and causes serotonin

00:13:27.960 --> 00:13:31.500
 to be released from the platelets,

00:13:31.500 --> 00:13:36.500
